\cf0 The DevOps movement started {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://medium.com/r/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FDevOps"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 in roughly 2008}} and was designed to address the gap between the development of software (dev) and the operation/use of said software (ops).\cf0  \
\
\cf0 Jez Humble explains that DevOps is\'a0:\cf0  \
\
\pard\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\tx7370\tx7937\tx8503\pardeftab1102\li1133\slleading120\pardirnatural
\cf0 a cross-disciplinary community of practice dedicated to the study of building, evolving and operating rapidly-changing resilient systems at scale.\cf0  \
